<bioghist encodinganalog="5451" id="a2"> <head>Historical Note</head><p>In
November of 1981 Pastor Ernest Pihl began surveying and calling on homes in
order to establish a new LCA congregation at the present site. In February of
1982, regular Sunday services began at Hillcrest Elementary School. Formal
organization took place on March 6, 1983 with 137 baptized members. The year of
1985 was spent making arrangements and preparations for building. Construction
began in February, 1986 with the anticipation of beginning the Fall Program in
the new facility. As of January 1, 1986, Holy Cross numbered 246 baptized and
165 confirmed. </p>
</bioghist> <scopecontent encodinganalog="5202_" id="a3"> <p>This folder
contains a booklet from the service of organization, a congregational
historical record, a bulletin from the organizational meeting in 1983.</p>
